  "title": "Project Engineer (Electrical / 5.5 Days) - WC2",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Handle site preparation and coordination, including the preparation and submission of relevant project documents.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with and manage multiple stakeholders such as clients, consultants, subcontractors, and vendors to ensure project objectives and requirements are achieved.</li>\n  <li>Communicate effectively across all levels to facilitate smooth collaboration and issue resolution.</li>\n  <li>Develop detailed work schedules, and plan manpower and resources to support project timelines.</li>\n  <li>Interpret engineering drawings and perform basic engineering design and calculations.</li>\n  <li>Oversee the implementation of safety management systems on site.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and provide updates on project progress through regular reporting.</li>\n  <li>Apply knowledge of Singapore standards and Codes of Practice to ensure compliance.</li>\n  <li>Perform any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the reporting manager.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
